  "detailed_description": [
    {
      "heading": "Gigabit Ethernet PoE Extender",
      "text": "The MikroTik GPeR (Gigabit Passive Ethernet Repeater) is a robust solution designed to extend Ethernet connections over long distances, making it ideal for high-rise buildings and expansive industrial complexes. By allowing Ethernet cable extensions up to 1,500 meters, the GPeR overcomes the standard 100-meter Ethernet limitation, ensuring reliable connectivity across vast areas. Its compact design and passive operation facilitate seamless integration into existing network infrastructures without the need for additional power sources or complex configurations. The GPeR supports both PoE input and output, adhering to 802.3af/at standards and accommodating a wide voltage range of 24-57V. This feature enables the device to receive power from a PoE-enabled source and, in turn, supply power to downstream devices, streamlining installations by reducing the need for separate power lines. The device's PoE passthrough capability can be disabled if the connected device does not support PoE, offering flexibility in various deployment scenarios."
    },
    {
      "heading": "Network Performance and Reliability",
      "text": "Equipped with two Gigabit Ethernet ports, the GPeR ensures high-speed data transmission, maintaining network performance even over extended distances. The device is designed to handle maximum output per port, with 2A for input voltages between 18-30V and 0.7A for 30-57V inputs, ensuring consistent power delivery to connected devices. Its robust construction and efficient power management contribute to enhanced network reliability and uptime. The GPeR is engineered to operate in a wide temperature range, from -40°C to 70°C, making it suitable for deployment in various environmental conditions. Its durable design ensures longevity and consistent performance, even in harsh climates. This versatility makes the GPeR an excellent choice for extending network connectivity in both urban and industrial settings, providing a reliable solution for complex networking challenges."
    }
  ],
